Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: In a recent issue of your paper I observed an article headed "Nokomai," in which your reporter states that "the squatting regulations are said to have driven the miners away" from this place, giving at the same time an instance in which this "arbitrary power" has been exercised in the case of a miner named Edge, who, says your reporter, by dint of steady perseverance had acquired "a few head of cattle," which the runholder caused him to remove under penalty of impounding for tresspass.
